To assure that your phone works properly while you travel, please verify the country of your current location so the correct country code can be applied. The current country can also be changed under Settings->Call settings-> Assisted dialling.

Assisted dialling allows easy dialling of international calls while roaming in another country. First set \'Reference country\' to your home location. You may also edit the Country code, International dialling digits (IDD) prefix, the National dialling digits (NDD) prefix, Area/city code and the National number length.
